By Ngozi Njoku  Lagos   –     Two men, Saviour Monday, 20, and Christian Dovile, 39, were on Thursday arraigned in Lagos for allegedly conspiring to beat up and steal from a man. Monday and Dovile, both labourers at Obanta Street, Mile 12, Lagos, are facing a three-count charge of conspiracy, assault occasioning harm and stealing before an Ogudu Magistrates’ Court. The prosecutor, Sgt. Lucky Ihiehie, told the court that the duo and three others now at large committed the offences on Aug. 26 at Agility area of Mile 12, Ketu. Ihiehie said that the complainant, Umoru Yahaya, a motor boy at Mile 12 Garage, reported the matter at Ketu Police Station in Lagos. “Yahaya said that by 8.00p.m on that day he went to Bolla area of Agility in Mile 12 to defecate and some boys numbering about five attacked him. “They beat him up and inflicted injury on his left leg, right hand and mouth. “They also stole a phone given to him by his customer as collateral and a cash sum of N9, 000,” he said. The prosecutor said that the offences contravened Sections 411, 173 and 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Monday, however, admitted committing the offence, while Dovile pleaded not guilty. The Magistrate, Mrs E. Kubeinje adjourned the case until Sept. 25 for facts and sentencing for the first accused- Monday. Kubeinje granted Dovile bail of N50, 000 with two sureties each in like sum. She adjourned the case until Oct. 8 for mention.